metadata.name: Syzers #374
metadata.description:
Syzers is a generative synthesizer project with sounds altered by Tone JS.

¬∑¬∑¬∑¬∑ On Tuesday, May 17, unsold editions will be burned ¬∑¬∑¬∑¬∑

Visually it consists of 16 layers, in which more than 350 elements are combined randomly, generating synthesizers with unique environments and landscapes.
As for the sound, 40 tracks were recorded with analog synthesizers that were then assigned to each of the modules. These, combined in groups of 4, provide thousands of possible combinations. 
In addition, these sounds will be further modified by code effects that will randomly vary their properties.

Click to listen to the sounds

Many thanks to @Jpupper and @Fipiaggio for help with programming the sound part and @Purespider for the template. 
"FXHASH PFP Token Generator" https://github.com/PureSpider/fxhash-pfp

for best resolution "open live" then use the "download image" button on the lower right corner ;)

metadata.name: Copenhagen Interpretation #101
metadata.description:
The Copenhagen Interpretation of quantum physics suggests that objects don't have physical properties until being observed.

In this generative piece by itsgalo and Sp√∏gelsesmaskinen, a set of objects are being held in "superposition" and finally positioned when observed and minted.

Use mouse/touch to zoom, pan, and rotate. Press 's' to grab a screenshot. Best viewed in Firefox.

metadata.name: Deconstructions #90
metadata.description:
Deconstructions is a further experiment with blending 3 colors and 3 different textures to create structural/abstract compositions. It's a search for beauty within asymmetrical/unsynchronized forms and disharmonic structures.


Probabilities;

- 18 compositions with variations.

- 2 background colors.

- 3 different particle starting placements.

- 21 different base color palettes. (1 monochrome) 

- 2 different alpha types; tangential & randomized.

- Different edges.

- Several starting positions and styles (wavy or straight).

Additional animation features with different shapes, angles, direction and style.


In live mode, press ‚Äòs‚Äô to save as .png (1500x2000 px)

It can take up to a minute to render or longer in low-performance computers. Enjoy the process!


Made with p5.js

metadata.name: Desert Solitude #36
metadata.description: "Desert Solitude" is an exploration of my love for crystals, architecture, being one with nature, escaping technology and becoming ok with the idea of being alone. The series was derived using diffusion Ai models and put together in a generative image composition on fx(hash) May 2022. 123 editions were made available.

metadata.name: Efflorescence #12
metadata.description:
Efflorescence is a piece that bridges between Pouya and Fatima's hand crafted tiles and Gorilla Sun's generative work, and reflects their collective love for patterns and colour. Efflorescence is a generative token that creates unique compositions by random arrangement of different tiles and the colorisation thereof.

This generative token would not have been possible without Zeno Zeng's SVG runtime for P5JS!

Press the down arrow button to export an SVG of the artwork. In live view stroke width can be adjusted by zooming in and out.

metadata.name: YouAreAMazing1.0 #14
metadata.description:
YouAreAMazing1.0 

 Playable, colorful, and often *very challenging* generative-art mazes.
   
 Each maze begins with an "intro" animation of its genesis when opened.
   
 Mazes range in size from from "normal" to "MASSIVE".
   They're made of colorful interconnected rooms.
   Some mazes are spacious, others are downright claustrophobic.
   Floors are colored using 1 of 16 palettes of varying rarities.
   
   Some mazes feature a cat.
   
   Each twist and turn of every maze is randomly chosen,
     so there are BILLIONS of possible mazes.
   
   
   
   ... oh yeah, they're also playable ...
   
   keyboard:
   wasd keys navigate
   'h' peeks (cheats)
   
   touchscreen:
   touch edges to navigate
   top-right corner to peek (cheat)
   
   
   To PRINT your maze, press 'p'
   This will temporarily display the maze & its features in monochrome
     and open the 'print' dialog.
   
   When you complete your maze, you may save a file
     to remind people that "amazing you are"!

metadata.name: Alienpillars #13
metadata.description:
"A rare type of bug that supposedly arrived on a cargo ship is destroying crops on planet Uctumi, in the binary system of Extronium. A wide variety of very resistant subspecies has mutated and it is necessary to study and identify all of them to obtain a gen-activated pesticide that will work on all of their variations. The pest department of the Uctumi central government is working hard on it, and they say that these strange critters are probably related to similar species that inhabited the planet Earth of the Solar system a long time ago and have spread over the galaxy."

My second piece using the p5.js raymarcher I wrote. The drawing is made of circles and lines based on the 3D data. I wanted to try something hairy as it's easy to draw lines aligned to the surface normal with this method. I also used a shader for the frame and the glitchy/sketch features.

Features 

body color: green-red-purple-yellow-blue-black
body tone: dark-light
spots color: orange-green-blue-yellow-white
hair tips: yes-no
hair #1: short-medium-long
hair #2: short-medium-long
head size: small-medium-large
head shape: long-spherical-wide
glitchy mode: 10% chance
sketch mode: 9% chance
